# Insecur Cursor Protocol

Follow the shared repo protocol. Do not create a Cursor-only workflow.

Composer 2.5 is the preferred workhorse for agent-ready implementation tickets in this repo. Use it
for well-scoped implementation work, while the orchestrator handles review, quality gates, and
escalation.

Read these before implementation work:

- `AGENTS.md`
- `CONTEXT-MAP.md`
- `docs/agents/repo-navigation.md`
- `docs/agents/environment-adapters.md`
- `docs/agents/workflow.md`
- `docs/agents/skill-usage.md`
- `docs/agents/autonomous-loop.md`
- `docs/agents/issue-tracker.md`
- the relevant `skills/*/SKILL.md`
- the Linear issue body and linked context docs

Use `docs/agents/repo-navigation.md` to find the current status doc, package owner, local context
file, and spec before broad searching.

Linear work must use team `INS` and label `zaks-io/insecur`.

Only implement issues that are:

- `Todo`
- `ready-for-agent`
- unblocked
- scoped to one PR

Before opening a PR, run or request `skills/insecur-local-code-review/SKILL.md` on the branch when
the environment supports it. Address blocking findings before PR handoff.

Use branch names like `ins-123-short-slug`. Open PRs titled `INS-123: Short summary`.

When the orchestrator sends `Changes Requested` feedback, continue in the same thread, branch, and
PR. Read the PR review comments, push fixes to the same PR, and move the issue back to `In Review`
when ready.

Stop and comment in Linear when product scope, security posture, credentials, provider approval, or
ADR decisions are missing.
